Model/Observer concept

Common interface for all classes implementing the Observer functionality in the Model/Observer design pattern. More...

Detailed Description

Common interface for all classes implementing the Observer functionality in the Model/Observer design pattern.

virtual void imod::IObserver::BeforeUpdate ( IModel *  modelPtr,
int  updateFlags,
istd::IPolymorphic *  updateParamsPtr 
) [pure virtual]

This function will be called before update of the observer contents occures.

Please note, that in some cases no following AfterUpdate can be called.

virtual bool imod::IObserver::IsModelAttached ( const IModel *  modelPtr = NULL) const [pure virtual]

Check if specified model is attached.

pointer to model object. If this pointer is NULL, any model is meaned.

Returns:
true, if modelPtr is attached yet to this observer, false otherwise.

Implemented in imod::CMultiModelBridgeBase, imod::CSingleModelObserverBase, and imod::CMultiModelObserverBase.

virtual bool imod::IObserver::OnAttached ( IModel *  modelPtr) [pure virtual]

This call back function will be called, if an observable object is about to be attached.

This function returns a true, if observable object is accepted by the implementation logic of the observer, otherwise the function returns a false.
